text: Don't talk about what you have done or what you are going to do.
author: Thomas Jefferson

text: Getting lost along your path is a part of finding the path you are meant to be on.
author: Robin Sharma

text: The moment you stop to think about whether you love someone, you've already stopped loving that person forever.
author: Carlos Ruiz Zafon

text: Abundance of knowledge does not teach men to be wise.
author: Heraclitus

text: Some people feel the rain. Others just get wet.
author: Bob Dylan

text: The biggest adventure you can ever take is to live the life of your dreams.
author: Oprah Winfrey

text: The older you get, the better you get. Unless you're a banana.
author: Betty White

text: Without the confidence, nothing can be accomplished.
author: Sathya Sai Baba
